# Datastore Parity Gaps Between Go tork and Rust twerk

This patch documents all identified parity gaps between the Go datastore
interface (`/tmp/tork-go/datastore/datastore.go`) and the Rust datastore
trait (`/home/lewis/src/twerk/tork/datastore/mod.rs`) and implementation
(`/home/lewis/src/twerk/datastore/postgres/mod.rs`).

---

## GAP 1: Page struct field name mismatch

### Go code (datastore.go:70-76):
```go
type Page[T any] struct {
    Items      []T `json:"items"`
    Number     int `json:"number"`
    Size       int `json:"size"`
    TotalPages int `json:"totalPages"`
    TotalItems int `json:"totalItems"`
}
```

### Rust code (tork/datastore/mod.rs:19-29):
```rust
pub struct Page<T> {
    pub items: Vec<T>,
    pub total: i64,        // Should be: total_items (matches Go's TotalItems)
    pub page: i64,         // Should be: number (matches Go's Number)
    pub size: i64,
}
```

### Expected fix:
Rename Rust Page fields to match Go naming:
- `total` -> `total_items`
- `page` -> `number`

