## GAP 2: Update methods use different callback patterns

### Go code (datastore.go:28,36,41,50):
```go
UpdateTask(ctx context.Context, id string, modify func(u *tork.Task) error) error
UpdateNode(ctx context.Context, id string, modify func(u *tork.Node) error) error
UpdateJob(ctx context.Context, id string, modify func(u *tork.Job) error) error
UpdateScheduledJob(ctx context.Context, id string, modify func(u *tork.ScheduledJob) error) error
```

### Rust code (tork/datastore/mod.rs:37,61,71,106):
```rust
fn update_task(&self, id: String, task: Task) -> BoxedFuture<()>;
fn update_node(&self, id: String, node: Node) -> BoxedFuture<()>;
fn update_job(&self, id: String, job: Job) -> BoxedFuture<()>;
fn update_scheduled_job(&self, id: String, job: ScheduledJob) -> BoxedFuture<()>;
```

### Expected fix:
Change Rust trait to use closure-based modify pattern like Go:
```rust
fn update_task(&self, id: String, modify: impl FnOnce(&mut Task) -> DatastoreResult<()>) -> BoxedFuture<()>;
fn update_node(&self, id: String, modify: impl FnOnce(&mut Node) -> DatastoreResult<()>) -> BoxedFuture<()>;
fn update_job(&self, id: String, modify: impl FnOnce(&mut Job) -> DatastoreResult<()>) -> BoxedFuture<()>;
fn update_scheduled_job(&self, id: String, modify: impl FnOnce(&mut ScheduledJob) -> DatastoreResult<()>) -> BoxedFuture<()>;
```

